1
00:01:02,688 --> 00:01:04,108
When people finish their day

2
00:01:04,690 --> 00:01:07,110
and hurry home,

3
00:01:07,901 --> 00:01:09,691
my day starts.

4
00:01:33,617 --> 00:01:36,197
My diner is open from midnight

5
00:01:36,544 --> 00:01:37,834
to seven in the morning.

6
00:01:39,275 --> 00:01:42,275
They call it "Midnight Diner."

7
00:01:44,179 --> 00:01:45,800
PORK MISO SOUP COMBO
BEER, SAKE, SHOCHU

8
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,226
That's all I have on my menu.
PORK MISO SOUP COMBO
BEER, SAKE, SHOCHU

9
00:01:47,226 --> 00:01:47,851
PORK MISO SOUP COMBO
BEER, SAKE, SHOCHU

10
00:01:48,034 --> 00:01:51,011
But I'll make whatever customers request

11
00:01:51,012 --> 00:01:53,330
as long as I have the ingredients for it.

12
00:01:53,330 --> 00:01:54,990
That's my policy.

13
00:01:59,948 --> 00:02:01,198
Do I even have customers?

14
00:02:01,832 --> 00:02:03,492
More than you would expect.

15
00:02:06,309 --> 00:02:09,147
MIDNIGHT DINER:
TOKYO STORIES

16
00:02:09,147 --> 00:02:14,507
NEW YEAR'S EVE NOODLES, AGAIN

17
00:02:20,147 --> 00:02:22,277
Before I know it, a year has passed.

18
00:02:22,694 --> 00:02:25,364
Another New Year's Eve is here.

19
00:02:29,039 --> 00:02:32,820
If you have six wins and four losses,
I call it a good life.

20
00:02:33,085 --> 00:02:34,795
Some great mind said so.

21
00:02:35,387 --> 00:02:36,427
Cheer up.

22
00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:40,203
Stop looking so miserable.

23
00:02:40,285 --> 00:02:42,375
It makes me feel cold.

24
00:02:43,455 --> 00:02:45,505
My empty wallet makes me feel frozen.

25
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:48,835
There are hot days and cold days.

26
00:02:49,150 --> 00:02:51,030
Feels like the middle of the desert.

27
00:02:51,446 --> 00:02:54,700
A good day is followed by a bad day.

28
00:02:54,700 --> 00:02:56,780
It's a rule of the universe.

29
00:03:00,122 --> 00:03:02,332
In the spring, the god of horse racing

30
00:03:03,125 --> 00:03:04,965
brought me a stroke of good fortune

31
00:03:05,585 --> 00:03:08,055
with cherry blossoms.

32
00:03:09,589 --> 00:03:10,759
Then winter came.

33
00:03:11,633 --> 00:03:14,013
My good fortune melted as it snowed.

34
00:03:16,007 --> 00:03:18,017
You're not a good gambler anyway.

35
00:03:19,036 --> 00:03:20,616
Here you go.

36
00:03:21,185 --> 00:03:23,667
Listen,
at least you had a good dream.

37
00:03:24,627 --> 00:03:26,757
But that caused Master trouble.

38
00:03:27,269 --> 00:03:28,099
What?

39
00:03:31,491 --> 00:03:36,331
Okay. Good. Keep moving.

40
00:03:37,326 --> 00:03:38,487
Hey, careful.

41
00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:42,040
That was like a sweet dream
on a warm spring day.

42
00:03:42,289 --> 00:03:43,539
This is fine here.

43
00:03:47,252 --> 00:03:49,962
- Clear.
- Come in.

44
00:03:51,404 --> 00:03:52,614
Welcome.

45
00:03:53,771 --> 00:03:56,271
Master, I did it.

46
00:03:56,855 --> 00:03:58,480
A million... A million...

47
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:00,430
You disappoint me, Komichi.

48
00:04:01,089 --> 00:04:04,730
- You stole money? A million?
- A million.

49
00:04:04,918 --> 00:04:08,388
He bet on a dark horse
at the Emperor Cup.

50
00:04:16,010 --> 00:04:18,325
I was going to bet
on the odds-on favorite,

51
00:04:18,325 --> 00:04:20,375
but I bet on the dark horse by mistake.

52
00:04:21,158 --> 00:04:25,158
At the beginning of the race,
the top horse fell down

53
00:04:25,207 --> 00:04:27,997
and caused a big mess.
The dark horse survived and won.

54
00:04:29,336 --> 00:04:33,166
- I'm so scared of my great fortune.
- Congratulations.

55
00:04:33,256 --> 00:04:35,724
Do anything you want with that.

56
00:04:35,857 --> 00:04:39,431
I've never seen or earned
such a large amount of money.

57
00:04:39,513 --> 00:04:40,928
I don't know what to do.

58
00:04:41,004 --> 00:04:43,924
At the very least,
let me treat you all tonight.

59
00:04:44,195 --> 00:04:45,195
No.

60
00:04:45,644 --> 00:04:49,272
- Thanks, but we have to go now.
- Why?

61
00:04:49,375 --> 00:04:51,795
We escorted him here.
Let's eat with his money.

62
00:04:51,876 --> 00:04:53,956
- She's right.
- That's inappropriate.

63
00:04:54,528 --> 00:04:57,108
We're detectives.
We're public servants.

64
00:04:57,197 --> 00:05:00,907
- It's a sign of our friendship, right?
- Of course, it's about friendship.

65
00:05:02,077 --> 00:05:03,037
It's...

66
00:05:03,328 --> 00:05:04,948
It's unconditional.

67
00:05:05,038 --> 00:05:08,998
It's based on an intimate relationship,
one in which we care for each other.

68
00:05:09,084 --> 00:05:11,844
- It's a beautiful...
- Friendship.

69
00:05:12,295 --> 00:05:13,885
If so, what would you do?

70
00:05:15,549 --> 00:05:18,129
If so, we should accept it.

71
00:05:19,302 --> 00:05:20,722
As a matter of courtesy.

72
00:05:21,805 --> 00:05:25,025
Master, serve them anything they want.

73
00:05:25,100 --> 00:05:27,350
- I want sushi.
- Wait.

74
00:05:27,436 --> 00:05:29,664
If you want sushi,
you should go elsewhere.

75
00:05:29,664 --> 00:05:30,504
But...

76
00:05:31,115 --> 00:05:36,037
I wish to share the joy
with everyone at your diner.

77
00:05:40,657 --> 00:05:43,617
Tonight's mixer was as pathetic as usual.

78
00:05:43,702 --> 00:05:46,061
All the men talk like feminists,

79
00:05:46,061 --> 00:05:49,945
but at the bottoms of their hearts
they think a woman is an ornament.

80
00:05:50,109 --> 00:05:52,554
Even in the 21st century,
nothing has changed.

81
00:05:52,653 --> 00:05:53,573
Fine!

82
00:05:54,337 --> 00:05:55,877
I will never marry.

83
00:05:57,393 --> 00:05:59,183
Here comes Greater amberjack.

84
00:06:04,551 --> 00:06:05,671
What's going on?

85
00:06:06,183 --> 00:06:08,890
Komichi won big on a horse race.

86
00:06:08,987 --> 00:06:10,907
So, he's treating everyone to sushi.

87
00:06:12,105 --> 00:06:13,155
Please join us.

88
00:06:13,607 --> 00:06:15,789
Really? Can we?

89
00:06:15,789 --> 00:06:19,579
You can eat anything you want, yes.
Everyone else, eat some more.

90
00:06:19,699 --> 00:06:21,765
- I'll have fatty tuna.
- Salmon roe for me.

91
00:06:21,765 --> 00:06:22,835
Coming right up.

92
00:06:28,997 --> 00:06:30,407
Mater, I'm sorry...

93
00:06:31,166 --> 00:06:32,496
about the big party.

94
00:06:33,793 --> 00:06:36,093
- This is an exception, okay?
- I know.

95
00:06:44,067 --> 00:06:47,567
It was the biggest event
among us this spring.

96
00:06:50,435 --> 00:06:53,985
In the summer,
we had a rare incident.

97
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:58,610
- The best summer food is watermelon.
- I agree.

98
00:06:59,795 --> 00:07:03,675
It'd be perfect
if we had anti-mosquito incense.

99
00:07:04,407 --> 00:07:05,617
I have the incense.

100
00:07:08,161 --> 00:07:09,871
Thank you for the salt.

101
00:07:10,914 --> 00:07:11,874
Here you go.

102
00:07:13,416 --> 00:07:16,586
This is it. It completes
a perfect Japanese summer.

103
00:07:29,641 --> 00:07:30,471
What?

104
00:07:31,476 --> 00:07:34,096
Are those the power-generating
wind bells?

105
00:07:35,188 --> 00:07:36,608
That's pretty.

106
00:07:41,319 --> 00:07:42,149
Boss.

107
00:07:42,654 --> 00:07:44,284
Relax.

108
00:07:44,364 --> 00:07:46,074
Maybe a wire shorted out.

109
00:07:47,409 --> 00:07:49,369
I wonder if our bar is okay.

110
00:07:49,911 --> 00:07:51,621
It's not an earthquake.

111
00:07:51,705 --> 00:07:53,465
I'm sure it won't last long.

112
00:07:54,416 --> 00:07:56,996
We'll make it through a while
with candles.

113
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:09,760
What can I say?

114
00:08:10,387 --> 00:08:13,847
This is like a horror night.

115
00:08:14,352 --> 00:08:17,442
Don't say that. I love horror stories.

116
00:08:18,148 --> 00:08:21,278
Can anyone tell a scary story?

117
00:08:22,777 --> 00:08:24,777
I don't know if it's scary or not.

118
00:08:25,322 --> 00:08:27,242
But it's about a watermelon.

119
00:08:27,324 --> 00:08:28,374
Want to hear it?

120
00:08:28,783 --> 00:08:29,833
Sure.

121
00:08:30,493 --> 00:08:33,663
This is what happened to

122
00:08:34,164 --> 00:08:35,664
my grandfather.

123
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:39,920
On a summer night 60 years ago,

124
00:08:40,587 --> 00:08:42,377
it was around this same time,

125
00:08:42,922 --> 00:08:45,929
my grandfather was having a drink
at his colleague's place

126
00:08:45,988 --> 00:08:47,488
where he lived alone.

127
00:08:48,178 --> 00:08:49,598
It was hot and humid.

128
00:08:50,096 --> 00:08:53,346
They ran out of liquor and food.
They were so thirsty.

129
00:08:53,933 --> 00:08:57,063
So, the colleague said,
"Let's go get a watermelon."

130
00:08:57,812 --> 00:08:59,062
Steal a watermelon?

131
00:09:00,690 --> 00:09:04,110
They were so drunk,
they entered a watermelon field.

132
00:09:04,587 --> 00:09:07,257
They each stole one,

133
00:09:07,364 --> 00:09:10,244
then headed back to the house
along a railway track.

134
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:12,640
They stumbled upon a graveyard,

135
00:09:13,148 --> 00:09:16,488
which they hadn't seen
when they entered the field.

136
00:09:17,248 --> 00:09:19,918
"I didn't know there was a graveyard."

137
00:09:20,377 --> 00:09:24,667
When they came to a halt,
a bright light appeared out of the blue.

138
00:09:24,756 --> 00:09:28,296
A train was not supposed to run that late,
but there was one coming.

139
00:09:29,111 --> 00:09:32,451
Then, my grandfather woke up
on the ground by the track.

140
00:09:32,847 --> 00:09:34,858
He must have jumped
away from the train.

141
00:09:34,858 --> 00:09:38,673
But he couldn't find his colleague.
No streetlights. It was pitch-black.

142
00:09:39,729 --> 00:09:43,979
He called, but got no answer. He thought
that the colleague left without him.

143
00:09:44,067 --> 00:09:47,655
So, my grandfather made his way
back to his colleague's house

144
00:09:47,655 --> 00:09:49,815
with the watermelon,
which was not damaged.

145
00:09:50,657 --> 00:09:53,827
When he tried to wash the watermelon,
he realized that...

146
00:09:54,285 --> 00:09:55,545
it was not a watermelon

147
00:09:56,329 --> 00:09:59,249
but the bloody head of his friend.

148
00:10:17,767 --> 00:10:19,387
Are you okay?

149
00:10:20,145 --> 00:10:23,155
- Ryu, are you okay?
- I got this as a gift.

150
00:10:23,277 --> 00:10:25,067
I wanted to share it with you all.

151
00:10:25,942 --> 00:10:26,942
Ryu...

152
00:10:41,750 --> 00:10:42,830
Hey, boss.

153
00:10:44,502 --> 00:10:46,194
Ever since that night,

154
00:10:46,413 --> 00:10:48,833
Ryu has been unable to eat watermelon.

155
00:10:50,008 --> 00:10:51,378
Poor Ryu.

156
00:10:56,931 --> 00:10:59,601
Autumn is the harvest season.

157
00:11:00,143 --> 00:11:03,273
Autumn is also the season of love.

158
00:11:03,897 --> 00:11:05,857
As it gets colder,

159
00:11:06,226 --> 00:11:08,140
you feel the need for company.

160
00:11:08,271 --> 00:11:10,271
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

161
00:11:10,904 --> 00:11:11,994
My mouth's watering.

162
00:11:12,489 --> 00:11:13,909
I will eat it.

163
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,910
It's can't be...

164
00:11:51,194 --> 00:11:54,404
A crime? It must be a crime.

165
00:11:54,489 --> 00:11:57,619
It could be an accident.

166
00:11:57,700 --> 00:11:59,870
It could be both.

167
00:11:59,953 --> 00:12:03,003
So, I have to go.
That's right. I have to go.

168
00:12:05,083 --> 00:12:06,463
Hello?

169
00:12:07,752 --> 00:12:09,922
Then another winter came.

170
00:12:10,338 --> 00:12:14,008
A year is about to end.

171
00:12:20,890 --> 00:12:21,720
Kasumi.

172
00:12:24,967 --> 00:12:26,307
Are you headed to work?

173
00:12:27,083 --> 00:12:29,413
This is a busy time of year.

174
00:12:29,769 --> 00:12:31,439
You should grab a good fortune.

175
00:12:31,861 --> 00:12:34,191
- Have a happy new year!
- You, too.

176
00:12:41,424 --> 00:12:43,254
Spring will come again after winter.

177
00:12:44,048 --> 00:12:46,241
I can't keep losing forever.

178
00:12:47,208 --> 00:12:49,929
I'll do my best to have
a good fortune next year.

179
00:12:50,012 --> 00:12:52,392
Good attitude. Have a drink.

180
00:12:52,898 --> 00:12:54,858
Forget all the failures.

181
00:12:55,479 --> 00:12:56,309
Thanks.

182
00:12:58,724 --> 00:13:01,144
- Good evening.
- Welcome.

183
00:13:02,217 --> 00:13:05,097
I knew you'd all be here.

184
00:13:05,995 --> 00:13:09,335
How pathetic. It's New Year's Eve.

185
00:13:09,478 --> 00:13:11,265
You don't have anywhere else to go?

186
00:13:11,411 --> 00:13:14,121
That's right. And neither do you.

187
00:13:14,514 --> 00:13:15,600
Buckwheat noodles?

188
00:13:15,682 --> 00:13:18,062
- Of course.
- Extra large, please.

189
00:13:18,214 --> 00:13:19,134
Sure.

190
00:13:25,931 --> 00:13:27,577
- Hello.
- Welcome.

191
00:13:27,647 --> 00:13:29,777
- Good evening.
- Good evening.

192
00:13:45,008 --> 00:13:46,258
It's so delicious.

193
00:13:47,722 --> 00:13:50,482
I'm so glad to eat noodles
before the new year arrives.

194
00:13:51,019 --> 00:13:54,149
After midnight, it's no longer
"New Year's Eve noodles."

195
00:13:54,317 --> 00:13:57,218
In some regions, they say
that it will bring you bad luck

196
00:13:57,218 --> 00:13:59,638
if you eat noodles after midnight.

197
00:14:00,124 --> 00:14:02,714
- Is that so?
- You know a lot, huh?

198
00:14:03,248 --> 00:14:05,458
- I got all from Wiki.
- Wiki?

199
00:14:06,733 --> 00:14:08,193
Is that some kind of monkey?

200
00:14:10,358 --> 00:14:11,988
It's Wikipedia.

201
00:14:12,669 --> 00:14:13,749
Pedia?

202
00:14:14,754 --> 00:14:17,974
Just the sound of it tells me
that it has nothing to do with me.

203
00:14:22,251 --> 00:14:25,171
- Hello.
- Welcome.

204
00:14:26,265 --> 00:14:27,525
What's that?

205
00:14:27,925 --> 00:14:30,845
We're going to Hawaii
on an early morning flight.

206
00:14:31,299 --> 00:14:33,509
New Year's Day in Hawaii?

207
00:14:34,443 --> 00:14:36,533
I thought Saipan
was good enough, but...

208
00:14:36,588 --> 00:14:39,298
I wanted to be like a celebrity in Hawaii.

209
00:14:39,298 --> 00:14:41,678
We're here to drink
until the flight leaves.

210
00:14:42,657 --> 00:14:45,237
- But before that...
- Master.

211
00:14:46,077 --> 00:14:47,367
Buckwheat noodles!

212
00:14:48,035 --> 00:14:48,955
Sure.

213
00:14:52,287 --> 00:14:55,667
I wonder why we started eating
buckwheat noodles on New Year's Eve.

214
00:14:56,493 --> 00:14:58,823
- A noodle store conspiracy?
- Buckwheat noodles

215
00:14:58,998 --> 00:15:01,517
are easier to cut off
than other noodles.

216
00:15:01,517 --> 00:15:05,607
So, we eat it to cut off
"misfortunes and disasters of the year."

217
00:15:06,031 --> 00:15:08,256
This practice was established
during Edo period.

218
00:15:08,487 --> 00:15:10,947
- You know so much.
- It's all from Wikipedia.

219
00:15:11,988 --> 00:15:15,748
It means that we shouldn't eat
chewy noodles like ramen?

220
00:15:17,037 --> 00:15:19,247
It's not easy to be cut off, huh?

221
00:15:24,623 --> 00:15:27,253
- Ryu!
- We escorted it.

222
00:15:28,441 --> 00:15:32,662
- Good evening.
- Wow, New Year's food.

223
00:15:44,992 --> 00:15:47,542
You are a slow eater as usual.

224
00:15:48,293 --> 00:15:51,923
If I eat quickly, I get heartburn.
I must be getting old, huh?

225
00:15:54,535 --> 00:15:57,005
Seems like the last New Year's Day
was yesterday.

226
00:15:57,813 --> 00:16:00,143
Before I know it, a year has passed.

227
00:16:00,829 --> 00:16:02,999
It gets faster once you turn 30.

228
00:16:03,143 --> 00:16:05,393
- Be prepared.
- I'm already in my 30s.

229
00:16:06,696 --> 00:16:07,616
I knew that.

230
00:16:11,297 --> 00:16:14,717
Nothing special happened this year.

231
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:18,450
You should know better.

232
00:16:19,571 --> 00:16:22,161
"Nothing special happened."
It means peace.

233
00:16:23,155 --> 00:16:27,995
We should appreciate it
if we have nothing special.

234
00:16:28,427 --> 00:16:29,347
That's right.

235
00:16:30,957 --> 00:16:32,584
Five.

236
00:16:32,585 --> 00:16:34,403
Four.

237
00:16:34,403 --> 00:16:35,813
Three.

238
00:16:35,813 --> 00:16:37,430
Two.

239
00:16:37,430 --> 00:16:39,024
One.

240
00:16:39,024 --> 00:16:41,654
Happy New Year!

241
00:16:42,252 --> 00:16:44,542
I wish you all the best
in this new year.

242
00:16:45,808 --> 00:16:49,108
- Then...
- Stop it. No alcohol.

243
00:16:49,508 --> 00:16:52,628
Let's have this. Soba stock.

244
00:17:05,174 --> 00:17:07,054
Happy new year.

245
00:17:23,276 --> 00:17:24,226
Master?

246
00:17:25,153 --> 00:17:27,863
The mistress will be a little late.

247
00:17:49,158 --> 00:17:50,698
When people finish their day

248
00:17:51,157 --> 00:17:53,247
and hurry home,

249
00:17:54,343 --> 00:17:56,053
my day starts.

250
00:17:57,174 --> 00:17:59,977
My diner is open from midnight

251
00:17:59,977 --> 00:18:01,437
to seven in the morning.

252
00:18:01,923 --> 00:18:05,593
They call it "Midnight Diner."

253
00:18:07,874 --> 00:18:10,964
Bye, Master. I look forward
to your goodwill in the new year.

254
00:18:11,490 --> 00:18:14,454
- Bye.
- Have a great trip.

255
00:18:14,454 --> 00:18:17,374
- Bye.
- Bye.

256
00:18:26,923 --> 00:18:28,463
I hope it goes well.

257
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:34,800
Michiru, what do you want for a souvenir?

258
00:18:35,097 --> 00:18:36,097
Come talk.

259
00:18:41,342 --> 00:18:44,222
Did you say that there was
a new Hawaiian pub?

260
00:19:03,827 --> 00:19:04,997
Happy new year.

261
00:19:14,387 --> 00:19:18,007
Thank you for helping me clean dishes.

262
00:19:18,833 --> 00:19:19,982
You're welcome.

263
00:19:19,982 --> 00:19:21,812
It was a busy day, so you need help.

264
00:19:25,183 --> 00:19:27,343
Master, you are a lucky man.

265
00:19:28,260 --> 00:19:30,760
You have so many great customers.

266
00:19:32,401 --> 00:19:33,441
You're right.

267
00:19:37,419 --> 00:19:39,607
You attract them.

268
00:19:39,607 --> 00:19:40,591
No.

269
00:19:41,231 --> 00:19:44,281
I just open the diner
at the same time every day,

270
00:19:44,807 --> 00:19:46,767
make whatever they want,

271
00:19:47,287 --> 00:19:49,966
and close the diner
at the same time every day.

272
00:19:49,966 --> 00:19:52,386
- That's all.
- Sounds like a great diner.

273
00:19:54,583 --> 00:19:55,427
Hey,

274
00:19:58,509 --> 00:20:01,089
care to make the first shrine visit
with me?

275
00:20:05,708 --> 00:20:06,966
Sorry.

276
00:20:08,601 --> 00:20:11,891
I was planning to do
a general house cleaning today.

277
00:20:15,703 --> 00:20:16,533
I see.

278
00:20:21,925 --> 00:20:23,045
I understand.

279
00:20:34,721 --> 00:20:37,641
I look forward to your continued
goodwill in the new year.

280
00:20:40,019 --> 00:20:40,889
You, too.

281
00:23:40,969 --> 00:23:45,976
THIS STORY IS FICTION

